Article 1 - Scope of application

ComPation age to aten hare honor set at contence thei -promotion of food products diversity and quality (including through geographical indications);

development of public policies regarding food safety, especially in areas of institutional organization, capacity building and human resources training development of the livestock sector, notably through technical and economic exchanges (notably animal nutrition and genetics) between the stakeholders of the livestock industry of the Parties;

promotion of sustainable agricultural practices (including agro-ecology and permaculture through technical and technology support to preserve soil and water resources, protect biodiversity, and provide instruments to adapt and mitigate the impacts of climate change:

exchanges of information, with SEMMARIS (company in charge of the management of the wholesale market of Pars-Rungis), for the creation of a wholesale agricultural products and food market in Clark Green City, notably for the implementation of a feasibility study.

structuring, organization and modernization of agricultural commodity chains (including strengthening of the cold chain);

sanitary and phyto-sanitary issues to facilitate trade:

laboratory capacity building physical design of laboratories and development optimization and validation of tests and methods for the detection and genetic characterization of pathogens (particularly for animal diseases pathogens);

provision of training and expertise to develop Chambers of Agriculture and cooperative systers in the Philippines

Specific technical cooperation projects are to be jointly developed and implemented by the Parties
